def is_prime(n):
    if n < 2:
        return False
    if n == 2:
        return True
    if n % 2 == 0:
        return False
    i = 3
    while i * i <= n:
        if n % i == 0:
            return False
        i += 2
    return True

Approach:
- n < 2: not prime by definition.
- n == 2: the only even prime.
- Even n > 2: divisible by 2, not prime.
- Check only odd divisors from 3 up to √n. If n = a × b with a ≤ b, then a ≤ √n, so we never need to check beyond √n.

Time complexity: O(√n).

